title: Serialize/MacroCallBlock-normalized
description: AST-only mode drops parameter spacing and separates block calls with a blank line
tags: $:/tags/wikitext-serialize-normalize-spec
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki-multiple

title: info

`one: val1` becomes `one:val1`, and consecutive block calls are separated
by one blank line.

Why: the AST records parameters as name and value pairs without the
whitespace around the colon, and block nodes carry no separators, so
tree-only serialization normalizes both.

* Covers: $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/wikitext-serialize/rules/macrocallblock.js and serializeAttribute in $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/wikitext-serialize/utils/parsetree.js.
* Mode: ast-only (the Input field withholds the source from the serializer).
+
title: Input
mode: ast-only

<<john one: val1 two: 'val "2"'>>

<<john>>
after
+
title: ExpectedWikitext

<<john one:val1 two:'val "2"'>>

<<john>>

after
